# Storywright environment variables
#
# Storywright does NOT require any environment variables for normal use.
# The Anthropic API key is entered in-app on first launch and stored in
# the browser's localStorage — it never reaches any server other than
# api.anthropic.com.
#
# This file exists for completeness and for the rare case where you want
# to bake a key into a development build (e.g. a kiosk demo). To use it:
#   1. Copy this file:    cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in the value below.
#   3. Restart the dev server.
#
# Vite only exposes vars prefixed with VITE_ to client code. The app does
# not currently consume this variable; if you need it, wire it into
# storywright.jsx where the API key is read.

# VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
